Reported results indicators by the European Commission ¿ International Cooperation and Development (DEVCO) may not represent the complete set of indicators monitored for the project. The results are reported using a contribution approach. This means that where a project has been financed by the EU jointly with other funders ¿ such as partner country governments or other donors ¿ the overall outputs of the collective effort are reported rather than outputs attributed to the share of funding provided by the EU. For higher levels of results, such as outcomes and impacts, the project will only have contributed to the overall effort.

Number of formal and informal jobs created directly through EUTF support, irrespective of the workers' status (formal, informal), whether it is considered as their main or a secondary job (part-time /full-time). 

Informal employment is characterized by a relationship that is not subject to national labour legislation, income taxation, social protection or entitlement to certain employment benefits. It encompasses employees holding informal jobs, employers and own-account workers employed in their own informal sector enterprises, members of informal producers¿ cooperatives, contributing family workers in formal or informal sector enterprises, and own-account workers engaged in the production of goods for own end use by their household.

A Trust Fund pools the funds of several donors to jointly finance an action on the basis of commonly agreed objectives and reporting formats. EU Trust Funds are EU-led tools, benefitting from fast decision-making processes and from their capacity to pool larger sums from different sources making them a flexible, proactive and adaptable tool. 
                                        The incoming funds value does not relate to a total pledges from Trust Funds donors, but shows an actually received contribution from those donors (EDF, Annual Budget and the EU Member States and other Non-EU Member states donors). More information about funds received by the EUTF are available at the following link http://ec.europa.eu/budget/library/biblio/documents/2018/DB2018_WD11_en.pdf
